caller_intent: Jennifer is seeking to transition her home insurance from Main Street America (exiting North Carolina) to a new provider, while also addressing auto insurance needs for her temporary home until January 2024.
resolution_steps: Brandi explains Main Street America's exit from NC due to financial losses and lack of rate increases.
Discusses Auto Owners as a home-only option with 100% replacement cost coverage and temporary policy benefits.
Explains National General's auto insurance options with specific deductibles and coverage details.
Clarifies refund process for unused months if the home is sold in January.
Provides cost comparisons between current Main Street America rates and new quotes.
knowledge_required: Insurance market changes (Main Street America's NC exit)
summary: Brandi assists Jennifer in transitioning from Main Street America to Auto Owners for temporary home insurance, explaining coverage upgrades and refund terms for a January 2024 home sale. Auto Owners' 100% replacement cost and 25% additional coverage are highlighted, while National General's auto insurance options with specific deductibles are discussed. The call concludes with Brandi offering to resend quotes for review.
